title: About me
text:
Hi, my name is Qin Ti. I’m a bioinformatician and currently work as a Research Assistant at Zhejiang University(ZJU), specializing in the realms of machine learning and bioinformatics, areas that captivate my interests deeply.
With a background in bioinformatics and data visualization, I possess adept skills in utilizing Python and R programming languages. Additionally, I possess a foundational understanding of Linux commands, having engaged in bulk and single-cell transcriptomics analyses.
Moreover, my guiding principle, “Humility in acknowledging one’s limitations marks the inception of transcending biases,” encapsulates my worldview and approach to navigating the intricacies of life.

title: Welcome to my blog!
text:
Hey! this is my personal website.
Here, you’ll discover pages dedicated to Notes, where I share insights on decoding biological complexities and creating compelling visual narratives from data.
Beyond the technical, this blog is a glimpse into my life - from personal adventures to reflections on the world.
Curious to learn more about the face behind the words? Here’s some info about me.
